title: ACC women's soccer team earns first win of year; BU clinches playoff spot
text:
Brandon Sun - PRINT EDITION ACC women's soccer team earns first win of year; BU clinches playoff spot 
The Assiniboine Community College Cougars women’s soccer team kept their playoff hopes alive with their first win of the Manitoba Colleges Athletic Conference season on Saturday. 
Elena Woronzow and Katie Zacharias scored for the Cougars (1-5-0) in Otterburne as they edged the Providence University College Pilots 2-1. PUC dropped to 1-5-0. On Sunday, ACC fell 7-0 to the Red River College Rebels (6-0-0) in Winnipeg.
